description.p:
It is a further aspect of the present invention to provide for a first method of producing the plastic liner comprising the following steps:
extruding a multilayer parison tube having at least one thermoplastic-based layer and an inner layer having a lower hydrogen diffusivity than said at least one thermoplastic-based layer;
clamping the parison tube into a hollow cavity mould;
blowing the parison against the cavity; and
removing the molded plastic liner from the mould.

It is yet another aspect of the present invention to provide for a second method of producing the plastic liner comprising the following steps:
extruding a multilayer parison tube having at least one thermoplastic-based layer;
clamping the parison tube into a hollow cavity mould;
blowing the parison against the cavity;
removing the molded plastic liner from the mould; and
coating the interior wall of the molded plastic liner with an inner layer having a lower hydrogen diffusivity than said at least one thermoplastic-based layer.

claim.claim-text:
A method of producing a plastic liner having a multilayered wall, comprising the steps of:
- extruding a multilayer parison tube having at least one thermoplastic-based layer and an inner layer having a lower hydrogen diffusivity than said at least one thermoplastic-based layer;
- clamping the parison tube into a hollow cavity mould;
- blowing the parison against the cavity; and
- removing the molded plastic liner from the mould.

A method of producing a plastic liner having a multilayered wall, comprising the steps of.
- extruding a multilayer parison tube having at least one thermoplastic-based layer;
- clamping the parison tube into a hollow cavity mould;
- blowing the parison against the cavity;
- removing the molded plastic liner from the mould; and
- coating the interior wall of the molded plastic liner with an inner layer having a lower hydrogen diffusivity than said at least one thermoplastic-based layer.
